BEIJING - China's Defence Ministry is assigning 10 satellites to help search for missing flight MH370, reports said. The Xi'an Satellite Control Centre in northwestern China reprogrammed the high-resolution satellites for full-time monitoring of weather, communications and search operations in the area where the Malaysia Airlines B-777 passenger jet disappeared, the ministry said. Pilots of two planes from Hong Kong spotted unidentified debris off the coast of Vietnam on Monday, reports said.  But it was not clear if the debris was linked to the missing plane, which had been en route from Kuala Lumpur to Beijing with 227 passengers and 12 crew on board. This article is older than 60 days, which we reserve for our premium members only. You can subscribe to our premium member subscription, here. Get full Bangkok Post printed newspaper experience on your digital devices with Bangkok Post e-newspaper.  Try it out, it's totally free for 7 days. 